headline: Live Nation (LYV): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q4 Earnings?
summary: Since April 2020, the S&P 500 has delivered a total return of 87.2%. But one standout stock has more than doubled the market - over the past five years, Live Nation has surged 225% to $122.66 per share. Its momentum hasn’t stopped as it’s also gained 9.9% in the last six months thanks to its solid quarterly results, beating the S&P by 20.4%.
